  "local_port": 34028,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I use the Wi-Fi on my windows phone (wp8.1) in BHU (hostels, departments, library)?",
  "response": "To use Wi-Fi on your Windows Phone (WP8.1) at Banaras Hindu University (BHU) in hostels, departments, or the library, you need to follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Connect to the Wi-Fi Network**\n   - Go to **Settings** on your Windows Phone.\n   - Tap on **Wi-Fi** and turn it on.\n   - Wait for the available Wi-Fi networks to appear. Look for the BHU Wi-Fi network (e.g., \"BHU-WiFi\" or a similar name).\n   - Select the network and tap **Connect**.\n\n### 2. **Log in to the BHU Portal**\n   - After connecting to the Wi-Fi, open a web browser (e.g., Internet Explorer).\n   - You will be redirected to the BHU Wi-Fi **login/authentication portal**. If not, try visiting a non-HTTPS website (e.g., `http://example.com`) to trigger the redirect.\n   - Enter your **BHU credentials** (username and password) provided by the university. These are usually the same credentials you use for other university services.\n   - After successful login, you should have access to the internet.\n\n### 3. **Troubleshooting**\n   - **No Redirect to Login Page:** If the login page doesn\u2019t appear automatically, try clearing the browser cache or using a different browser.\n   - **Weak Signal:** Ensure you are in an area with strong Wi-Fi coverage. Move closer to the router if possible.\n   - **Incorrect Credentials:** Double-check your username and password. If you\u2019ve forgotten them, contact the BHU IT support team.\n   - **Network Issues:** If the Wi-Fi network is not working, it might be down or overloaded. Report the issue to the university IT department.\n\n### 4. **Additional Notes**\n   - Some university Wi-Fi networks may have restrictions on certain websites or services. If you encounter such issues, check the university\u2019s Wi-Fi usage policy.\n   - Ensure your Windows Phone is updated to the latest version of WP8.1 for optimal compatibility.\n   - If you face persistent issues, contact the BHU IT support team for assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to connect and use Wi-Fi on your Windows Phone at BHU.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
